casebody.data:
William Dempsey, Appellant v. John Heaney, Respondent. Decided November 10, 1891. Appeal from order vacating order for examination of defendant before trial. Edmund Luis Mooney, for appellant. Bernard Metzger, Metzger, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Dugro, J.

Per Curiam.

No necessity appears for the examination. Order affirmed, with $10 costs.
